This project highlights the modeling of an advanced, multi-pointed geometric
structure generated within the parametric CAD environment of Onshape, as visualized in STAR.
Representing a complex exercise in three-dimensional symmetry and spatial reasoning, the design consists
of a compound polyhedral stellation. Multiple faceted star-like prisms intersect at a single, centralized core, 
demonstrating advanced CAD modeling proficiency through the seamless 
merger of overlapping solid bodies without visual gaps.
To achieve this level of geometric intricacy, the design heavily relies on custom reference planes and
multi-axis patterning tools. Each individual spike features sharp, tapers that converge from a broad base to a crisp vertex,
accentuated by defined chamfered edge boundaries that enhance the model's visual depth. By establishing precise angular
offsets and using circular patterning features around a shared origin, perfect mathematical symmetry was maintained across
the X, Y, and Z axes. This project serves as an excellent demonstration of complex boolean operations, 
surface angling, and advanced feature duplication techniques within Onshape.
